Rating: 0
This is similar to a dip I have been making for years---if you want a fantastic smoked salmon dip everyone will love, try this: 1 container whipped cream cheese, 1/4 cup sour cream, 4ounces smoked salmon (chopped into small strips), 4 tablespoons chopped fresh dill. Mix the ingredients together and taste to see if the dill flavor is strong enough, then let the dip sit in the fridge several hours for the flavors to meld. I use leftover dill sprigs as garnish, but I am sure the caviar would make a nice garnish as well. Serve with thin pumpernickel slices, water crackers, bagel slices, or bagel chips. Enjoy!

