Rating: 4
This continues to be a favorite. Upon our returns from New York City, we bring some of our favorite Nova Salmon from Zabars. I always save a few slices for this dip. We prefer the dip without the caviar which makes it very salty - however, the caviar does make for a great presentation. I use whipped chive cream cheese as someone suggested, but added the chives listed in the recipe as well. I also tried using lemon juice and Tabasco and liked that as well. We prefer serving this with crackers, as a spread, when serving it at home, but use it as a dip when we take it to a party.

